Name Rascal/Libraries/Prelude/IO/iprint
Synopsis Print an indented representation of a value.
Function void iprint(value arg)
Usage import IO;
Description See iprintExp for a version that returns its argument as result and iprintln for a version that adds a newline.
Examples 
rascal>import IO;
ok
rascal>iprint(["fruits", ("spider" : 8, "snake" : 0), [10, 20, 30]]);
[
  "fruits",
  ("spider":8,"snake":0),
  [10,20,30]
]ok
